item.title: Help with port forwarding
item.dc:creator: @Telenim Telenim
item.description:
@Telenim wrote:

If you get this message when you try to type ipconfig in CMD

'ipconfig' is not recognized as an internal or external command, operable program or batch file.
You have to open “C:\WINDOWS\System32” then look for the file called “cmd.exe” and run that. Commands like ipconfig should work in that, just make a shortcut to that on your desktop if you ever need to use it again.

But if that isn’t what’s wrong, I have no idea. You can finish portforwarding without having to do that though, just find out what router you have and look up a guide at www.portforward.com
